  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering activities. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically obligated to report suspicious transactions to designated authorities. Specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Identifying and documenting suspicious financial activities\n3. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n4. Conducting customer due diligence\n5. Maintaining transaction records\n\nHowever, I want to be clear that I can discuss this topic generally, but cannot provide specific legal advice about reporting requirements.",
